Interactive (az login)Service Principal (environment variables)Workload Identity / OIDC <pre><code>az login
# Ansible will use your current az CLI session
</code></pre> <p><pre><code>export AZURE_CLIENT_ID=&lt;app-id&gt;
export AZURE_CLIENT_SECRET=&lt;client-secret&gt;
export AZURE_TENANT_ID=&lt;tenant-id&gt;
export AZURE_SUBSCRIPTION_ID=&lt;subscription-id&gt;
</code></pre> Use this for pipelines. See CI/CD Pipelines for pipeline-specific guidance.</p> <p>Configure a federated credential on the app registration and use: <pre><code>export AZURE_CLIENT_ID=&lt;app-id&gt;
export AZURE_TENANT_ID=&lt;tenant-id&gt;
export AZURE_SUBSCRIPTION_ID=&lt;subscription-id&gt;
# No AZURE_CLIENT_SECRET needed with federated identity
</code></pre></p> <p>Deployed resources always use Managed Identity</p> <p>The CI/CD pipeline identity (service principal) is only used to deploy resources. The deployed Logic Apps and connections authenticate to Azure services via Managed Identity — no client secrets are stored in Azure resources.</p>
